'''CloudBioLinux''' is an open-source project providing machine images for [[bioinformatics]] on [[cloud computing]] platforms.<ref name="CBL primary paper">{{Cite journal | last1 = Krampis | first1 = K. | last2 = Booth | first2 = T. | last3 = Chapman | first3 = B. | last4 = Tiwari | first4 = B. | last5 = Bicak | first5 = M. | last6 = Field | first6 = D. | last7 = Nelson | first7 = K. E. | title = Cloud BioLinux: Pre-configured and on-demand bioinformatics computing for the genomics community | doi = 10.1186/1471-2105-13-42 | journal = BMC Bioinformatics | volume = 13 | pages = 42 | year = 2012 | pmid = 22429538| pmc =3372431 }}</ref> CloudBioLinux provides a build and deployment system which can deploy directly to desktop machines, to desktop [[virtual machine|Virtual Machines (VMs)]], or to cloud providers such as the [[Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud]] (EC2). The project also provides a pre-built [[Amazon Machine Image]] (AMI) for use on Amazon EC2, and downloadable pre-built [[virtual machine image]]s for the desktop virtual machine software [[VirtualBox]] and for use on a private [[Eucalyptus (computing)|Eucalyptus]] cloud.
==Related projects==
[[BioLinux]] provides linux distributions configured for bioinformatics. The CloudBioLinux project grew out of the BioLinux project.<ref name="CBL primary paper"/>
The open-source CloudMan project builds on CloudBioLinux and [[Galaxy (computational biology)|Galaxy]] to provide pre-configured Galaxy virtual clusters on cloud computing platforms.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Afgan | first1 = E. | last2 = Chapman | first2 = B. | last3 = Taylor | first3 = J. | title = CloudMan as a platform for tool, data, and analysis distribution | doi = 10.1186/1471-2105-13-315 | journal = BMC Bioinformatics | volume = 13 | pages = 315 | year = 2012 | pmid = 23181507| pmc =3556322 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | last1 = Afgan | first1 = E. | last2 = Chapman | first2 = B. | last3 = Jadan | first3 = M. | last4 = Franke | first4 = V. | last5 = Taylor | first5 = J. | doi = 10.1002/0471250953.bi1109s38 | chapter = Using Cloud Computing Infrastructure with CloudBioLinux, CloudMan, and Galaxy | title = Current Protocols in Bioinformatics | year = 2012 | isbn = 0471250953 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>
